# Although, CMake will select a generator, if not specified.
# You may specify a generator when building your project.
# Use CMake --help to see available generator options, such as
# UnixMakefiles, Ninja, and more.

cmake -G <generator> -S <src> -B <build>

# Visual Studio support a more in-depth specification of a toolset.
# CMake will scan environment variables that override the defaults: 
# CMAKE_GENERATOR_TOOLSET and CMAKE_GENERATOR_PLATFORM. Alternatively, 
# the values can be specified directly in the command line: 

cmake -G <generator>
      -T <toolset>
      -A <platform>
      -S <src> -B <build>

# Here is an example command..

cmake \                        <<<Backslash allows multi-line
  -G "Visual Studio 17 2022" \
  -T ClangCL \
  -A x64 \
  -S . \
  -B build

# To check which generators are available on your system

cmake --help

